text.tspan: One night, a cucumber thief crept up to a cucumber
garden, to steal cucumbers, and thought:
First, steal cucumbers, sell the cucumbers, buy a
hen, hen lays eggs, eggs hatch chicks, sell chicks
for a pig, pig has piglets, sell piglets for a cow, cow
has calves, sell calves for a cucumber garden, sell
cucumbers, hire cucumber guards, who will shout
"HALT THIEF!" should anyone be FOOLISH enough
"HA HA HA!" the thief laughed triumphantly at his own
cleverness, to which someone shouted "HALT THIEF!"

tspan.tspan: Stories for Children by Leo Tolstoy, 1904, adapted
